\pard\plain \ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 We did grass drills at a hundred and six in teh sun. We attacked the blocking sleds and strutted through the intersecting ropes. We stood in what was called the shute and we went one on one, blocker and pass-rusher, and hand-fought each toher to the earth. Butted, clawed and kicked. There were any number of fistfights. There was one sprawling free-for-all, which the coaches allowed to continue for about five minutes, standing on the sidelines looking pleasantly bored as we kicked each other in the shins and threw dumb rights and lefts at caged faces, the more impulsive taking off their helmets and swinging them at anithing that moved. In the evenings we prayed.}}